text: The Cathedral of St Mary of the Assumption () is the Roman Catholic cathedral of the Spanish city of Ceuta located in a small exclave on the north coast of Africa. The cathedral is a 15th-century structure, built on the site of a sixth-century Christian church. The cathedral contains works of art dating from the 17th century to the present day. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in Spain Category:Ceuta Category:15th- century buildings and structures
title: Ceuta Cathedral
